##The fire line can not only focus on "dazzling" technology, these "bitter" disciplines provide an important guarantee for the national economy and people's livelihood —— An interview with the General Commander of Huashan Hospital Medical Team in Hubei Province, Professor Maxin

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Dictation Line

As soon as a large-scale public health event happens, these key "hard" subjects will provide an important guarantee for the national economy and people's livelihood, even for the survival of the nation.

Reporter | Huang Qi

Wuhan new crown pneumonia treatment pressure to ease, whether ordinary citizens or health care workers, are looking forward to the day of complete end of the epidemic as soon as possible.

The Mount Hua Hospital affiliated to Fudan University has sent four support Hubei medical teams to work in various medical institutions in Wuhan. The elite medical force of 273 people has been fighting in Wuhan for more than a month.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Some members of the Hubei medical team from Mount Hua Hospital take a group photo in Wuhan

As commander-in-chief of the Mount Hua Hospital's four-support Hubei Medical Team, ma Xin, deputy director of the Mount Hua Hospital, was interviewed by the magazine Xinmin Weekly on February 13. "How can a shelter hospital cope with the situation? " Asked Ma Xin, General Commander of the Hubei Medical Team of the Mount Hua Hospital, the epidemic situation and treatment in Wuhan at that time were introduced.

More than 20 days later, what is the current situation of the ICU ward of Wuchang's Shelter Hospital and Tongji Medical College Tongji Hospital affiliated to Tongji Medical College, which are under the responsibility of the medical team of Mount Hua Hospital? Personally participate in the fight against the new crown disease more than a month after President Maxin what is the feeling? On the afternoon of March 5, Vice President Maxin once again accepted an exclusive interview with Xinmin Weekly.

Some of the shelter beds are empty

Patients with complex conditions continue to be treated or transferred to hospital

Ma Xin, deputy director of Mount Hua Hospital

"Xinmin Weekly" : Wuhan has part of the Shelter Hospital closed, Mount Hua Hospital medical team to manage the Wuchang Shelter Hospital, the patient is not also reduced?

MAXIN: We have significantly fewer patients than before. Wuchang's shelter hospital used to have three sections, ABC. A week ago, section B was closed. There were 800 beds, there are now 500 beds, and 500 beds have only 200 patients, half of which are empty.

The Mount Hua Hospital medical team has 250 beds and now has fewer than 100 patients.

"Xinmin Weekly" : recently, many hospitals have found that their discharged patients have positive nucleic acid retests. Are there any such patients under the management of the medical team of Mount Hua Hospital?

MAXIN: We also followed up 2 patients who tested positive for nucleic acid but had no symptoms. This phenomenon shows that it is necessary to isolate them for another 14 days after discharge. After we noticed this phenomenon, we are also studying strategies to deal with it. For example, we raised the standard of two negative nucleic acid tests to three negative nucleic acid tests before discharge. Currently, the bed is more spacious, so patients can have a nucleic acid test, and throat swab sampling should be more standardized, and throat swab sampling training should be strengthened to improve accuracy. We're exploring the idea of testing it three times to see if we can get better results.

Patients in Shanghai have been discharged for an anal swab test to improve the success rate of the test, and we are actively exploring the feasibility of a shelter hospital.

Xinmin Weekly: Is it more complicated for patients who haven't been discharged?

MAXIN: We have not discharged patients, there are more than 10 patients after treatment continued positive nucleic acid testing. Patients like this are difficult to treat and we will consider transferring them to a designated hospital for further treatment.

There are some patients with complications, which means his NPV nucleic acid test is negative, but there are other complications, and there's still inflammation in the lungs, so we're not rushing to discharge him.

Maxin is in the shelter hospital

Xinmin Weekly: The number of patients continues to decrease. Does the stress of the medical staff decrease a lot?

Maxin: On the whole, the work pressure of medical staff is a little bit easier, but at this time whether it is the treatment of patients or medical staff on their own protection can not be taken lightly. So far, the Mount Hua Hospital medical team has maintained zero deaths and zero infections among the staff at Wuchang's shelter hospital, but after more than a month of work, some people may relax and think they should be fine without infection for so long, for example, take off the protective clothing when the action is faster, these lax ideas and actions can not have.

'Upriver' brings fewer critical cases

Improved treatment

Xinmin Weekly: The ICU ward of Guanggu district is full of critically ill patients. Has there been any change in the treatment of critically ill patients since the release of the Autopsy Report on the new pneumonia?

MAXIN: Some of the phenomena mentioned in the anatomical conclusions, we have found in the clinical treatment. For example, we found that the patient had a lot of sticky sputum in the upper airway, which was very sticky and difficult to cough up. It's consistent with the autopsy report.

Treatment, we have found that the disease is not only lung problems, many patients have heart, kidney, liver involvement, critically ill patients to do multi-organ treatment.

Xinmin Weekly: Is there less pressure to treat critically ill patients?

MAXIN: After this period of treatment, ICU critically ill patients less than before, some critically ill patients after treatment became critically ill, severe disease can be alleviated, you can transfer to the general ward. On the other hand, the number of critically ill patients "upstream" is not as high as before. This shows that the whole treatment system in Wuhan slowly straighten out, mild patients were treated in time, there will not be so many severe cases.

At the peak of the pressure, ICU30 beds, 27 patients with Endotracheal intubation, 3 on ECMO, 14 on hemodialysis, you can imagine the pressure of this rescue.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the early morning of February 27, a critically ill patient with new coronary pneumonia, old Cheng, was successfully evacuated after 9 days and nights of ECMO rescue in the ICU of Guanggu Hospital District of Wuhan Tongji Hospital

Xinmin Weekly: a few days ago, an ECMO patient in the ICU ward of Guanggu district was successfully taken offline. How is he doing?

MAXIN: the first Ecmo off-line patient, the recovery is very good, can spontaneous breathing, consciousness is also very conscious, these two days he can go to the general ward. We have one more patient coming up, and we're about to remove the ECMO. To be able to successfully ECMO offline is very difficult and difficult. So far, very few ECMO patients have successfully gone offline.

Xinmin Weekly: When do you think the work of the medical team will come to an end in the light of the current situation?

Maxin: We doctors always take the worst case into consideration. Now the numbers are going down, but there's no guarantee that they'll go up if something goes wrong. We can't take it lightly. We can't be too confident. Keep your The Hours on this string and keep your eyes open.

Resources should be tilted toward the "bitter" specialty

A lesson can not be repeated

Xinmin Weekly: After more than a month in Wuhan, what lessons do you think need to be learned from this epidemic?

MAXIN: This epidemic situation can really bring us a lot of thinking.

First of all, I think that the shelter hospital, as a form of emergency response to public health events, should become a strategic reserve in urban construction in the future. For example, the stadium, large venues, future design and construction of the need to consider whether it can be requisitioned for asylum or admission of patients.

Speaking of strategic reserve, another important reserve is special disciplines and talents.

In this case, infectious diseases, respiratory diseases, critical care, and other disciplines, and the people they had, played a very important role, and in the event of such an outbreak or disaster, these disciplines became very important.

Over the years, some hospitals have lost their infection departments. These departments work busy, pressure, income is not high, many people do not want to do, some hospitals are not willing to develop. These departments may not "make money" in hospitals. We sometimes think of the high-end scientific disciplines, the value of those special "dazzle" technology. However, as soon as a large-scale public health event occurs, these key "hard" disciplines will provide an important guarantee for the national economy and people's livelihood, and even the survival of the nation.

So hospitals have to tilt their resources toward these disciplines, and the state has to tilt even more toward these disciplines.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In October 2019, Huashan hospital conducted a drill for handling respiratory infectious disease patients

"The Xinmin Weekly" : "for a thousand days, for a time" , what other preparations does the medical system usually have to make?

MAXIN: to deal with large-scale epidemic situation and disaster, hospital should do well in process management.

Last October, a drill was held to prepare for the outbreak of a major infectious disease, an activity that we do every year. But I know not every hospital has this kind of rehearsal, I think every hospital should do.

Speaking of coincidences, in our October exercise, we simulated a patient coming back from abroad who had a fever and went to the hospital. The doctor suspected that he was a patient with an imported sexually transmitted disease. Our pre-check-up nurse in the emergency department found this problem, he was immediately directed to the fever clinic where doctors and nurses put on protective clothing and examined the patient. The medical staff sent the patient to the Radiology Department for imaging examination. The examination department also examined his related specimens. The patient was sent to the negative pressure ward of the infection department immediately after finding the problem.

I was the commander-in-chief of the drill, and I remember my colleagues holding up a sign that said "outbreak drill, " in case the onlookers got the wrong idea.

Two months later, there was a new outbreak of pneumonia, and everyone said our usual drills were too important.

Because of this drill, the Mount Hua Hospital can safely send experts to Wuhan, Professor Zhang Wenhong can safely go to the designated hospital in Shanghai, our own hospital departments in accordance with established procedures to deal with the epidemic smoothly. We are very familiar with the process of infectious diseases, usually our hospital sense management is very standard, management process is very mature, prepared to be safe.

The worst thing is to be unprepared. If normally there is no preparation, the epidemic came, everyone like a headless fly, there will be a great loss, if the medical staff with flesh and blood to fight this virus, the results must be very tragic, so must be scientific epidemic prevention.

Xinmin Weekly: What Role Does the sensory control specialty play in the epidemic?

MAXIN: the first thing the Mount Hua Hospital medical team should do is to have experts in hospital sense control management. They are the "protectors" of our other medical staff. They're like deminers, only the sense management guys know where the mines are, and they're going to give us a safe path forward, a scientific way to fight the epidemic, step by step, a safe way forward.

Just now, the leaders of the National Health Commission visited Guanggu Hospital district and gave a very high appraisal to the medical team of Mount Hua Hospital. These achievements are the reflection of our ordinary training, ordinary management and technical level.

Wuhan new coronary pneumonia treatment of a lot of experience, go back to a good summary, should be written into the textbook.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Maxin and Tongji Hospital Group photo, new crown pneumonia epidemic, Hubei medical staff have more than 3000 people infected

Xinmin Weekly: How do you feel about the new pneumonia epidemic, which has caused great losses to patients and society?

MAXIN: We have a lot of experience also have a lot of lessons, lessons can not repeatedly become a lesson, we had better sum up the experience in the growth, not through painful lessons to progress. In this epidemic, there are a lot of familial infections, a typical cluster infection, the family is sick, too affect the well-being of a family, which is very sad.
